üìù Easy Explanation
üîπ throws
Declares that a method may throw an exception
Does not handle it inside the method
üîπ try-catch
Handles the exception where method is called
üîπ ArithmeticException
Automatically thrown when dividing by zero
üîë One-Line Exam Answer
throws declares the exceptions a method might throw, letting the caller handle them.
